SIMPLE: nerveless
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: nerveless
<hw>nerve"less</hw> <pr>(n⟦etil⟧rv"l⟦ecr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of nerves.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Destitute of strength or of courage; wanting vigor;
weak; powerless.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A kingless people for a <qex>nerveless</qex> state.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Awaking, all <qex>nerveless</qex>, from an ugly dream.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nervelessness</ent>⟦br⟧
